  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to contrast and evaluate the functional outcome of patients with
      operative vs. nonoperative treatment of scapula fractures. The specific aim of this project
      is to monitor the return to function of patients in both the operative and nonoperative
      cohorts.

      The potential impact is a clearer set of choices in treatment options for this type of
      injury.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
